{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χορός</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>dance,</b> αἰεὶ δ᾽ ἡμῖν δαίς τε φίλη κίθαρίς τε χοροί τε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.248; μετὰ μελπομένῃσιν ἐν χορῷ Ἀρτέμιδος 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.183; τοὶ δ᾽ ἄνδρες ἐν ἀγλαΐῃς τε χοροῖς τε τέρψιν ἔχον 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 272, compare 277; εἰς χ. ἐλθέμεν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.508, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.194; οὐδέ κε φαίης ἀνδρὶ μαχεσσάμενον τόν γ᾽ ἐλθεῖν, ἀλλὰ χορόνδε ἔρχεσθ᾽ ἠὲ χοροῖο νέον λήγοντα καθίζειν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.393, 394; χορῷ καλὴ Πολυμήλη 16.180 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: later of the <b>dance</b> as a public religious ceremony, Διόνυσον τιμώσας χοροῖς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 220; φυλῆς Ἀκαμαντίδος ἐν χοροῖσιν 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 148, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.48, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χοροὺς ἀνῆγον αἱ πόλεις (i.e. εἰς τὴν Δῆλον) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.104 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>πεν-</b> ἀνδρῶν χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 147, cf. Scholia 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.10 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κύκλιος χ. (see. κύκλιος); θυσίῃσί σφεα (i.e. Δαμίην καὶ Αὐξησίην) καὶ χοροῖσι γυναικηΐοισι κερτόμοισι ἱλάσκοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.83; ἵστασαν χοροὺς παρθένων τε καὶ ἠϊθέων [prev. author] 3.48; παιδικὸς χ. 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 7.40, etc.; χ. ἀνδρικός 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.4.16, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 665b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τραγικοὶ χοροί, at Sicyon, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.67 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence of the <b>chorus</b> in the Attic drama, οἱ χ. τῶν τραγῳδῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 787, compare “Pax” 807 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. τραγικός, κωμικός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1276b4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; also χ. τρυγικός, τρυγῳδικός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 628 (_anapaest meter_), 886 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; arranged in six rows, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 173 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὃς οὐκ ἔδωκ᾽ αἰτοῦντι Σοφοκλέει χορόν (of the archon to whom the poet applied) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 15; χ. αἰτεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 513 (_anapaest meter_); διδόναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 383c, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χορὸν λαβεῖν, ἔχειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 94, “Pax” 803, 807 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. συλλέξαι, χοροὺς ἀθροίζειν (i.e. from the tribe), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.11, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 9.4; [χοροὺς] διδάσκειν [prev. passage]; χορὸν εἰσάγειν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 11: general phrases, χοροὺς ἱστάναι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.48 (see. above), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 280; ἔστασεν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 9.114; ἱερὸν χ. ἵστατε Νύμφαις 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 271 (_anapaest meter_), compare “Av.” 220 (_anapaest meter_); ἅψαι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 307 (_anapaest meter_); χορῶν κατάστασις [prev. author] “Ag.” 23, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 958; τοῖς χ. νικᾶν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.4.3; χοροῦ προεστάναι [prev. passage]; χορῷ χορηγεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 482b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>choir, band of dancers and singers, h. Ven.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 118, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.23, “fragment” 199; συμφωνία καὶ χοροί NT.Luke.15.25. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>choir, troop,</b> ἰχθύων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 762; μελιττῶν 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 5.13; χ. καλλίμορφος τέκνων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 925, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 315b, “Tht.” 173b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of things, ἄστρων αἰθέριοι χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 467 (Lyric poetry), compare 2nd c.AD: Mesomedes Lyricus “Hymnus in Solem” 17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. σκευῶν <b>row</b> of dishes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 8.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. δονάκων <b>row</b> of reeds, i. e. Pan's pipe, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Coluthus Epicus 124 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; χ. ὀδόντων <b>a row</b> of teeth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “de Usu Partium” 11.8 (hence οἱ πρόσθιοι χοροί,\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] for the front teeth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 548)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν σοφίαν ποῦ χοροῦ τάξομε; in what <b>class</b> shall we place it? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 279c, compare 6th c.AD: Choricius Rhetor 12.28 p.160 F.-R. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>place for dancing,</b> ἐν δὲ χ. ποίκιλλε.. Ἀμφιγυήεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.590; λείηναν δὲ χ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.260, compare 264; ὅθι τ᾽ Ἠοῦς ἠριγενείης οἰκία καὶ χοροί εἰσι 12.4; Νυμφέων καλοὶ χ. ἠδὲ θόωκοι [prev. work] 318 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; at Sparta the ἀγορά was called χορός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 3.11.9; so perhaps in Crete, “Supp.epigram” 2.509.6 (Eltynia, probably 5th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: see below (Acc. to [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus χορός\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>] ={κύκλος},{στέφανος}, and therefore properly denotes <b>a ring-dance.</b>)","strongNumber":"G5525","accentedUnicode":"χορός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5524","matchingForm":"χορηγέω","stepTransliteration":"chorēgeō","gloss":"to provide","_zh_tw_Gloss":"供應","_es_Gloss":"proveer","_zh_Gloss":"供应"}],"shortDef":"- = a ring, i.e. round dance (\"choir\")","mediumDef":"- = a ring, i.e. round dance (\"choir\")","stepGloss":"a dance","stepTransliteration":"choros","count":1,"_es_Definition":"baile","_zh_tw_Definition":"舞蹈, 跳舞 #路 15:25|","_zh_Definition":"舞蹈, 跳舞 #路 15:25|","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"nhảy múa.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"跳舞","_es_Gloss":"una danza","_zh_Gloss":"跳舞"}]}